Course Information

Short Intro

This course provides practical tutorials for Computer Networking, based on eNSP software from Huawei.

Prerequisites

We expect you to have the following skills before taking this course:

Required：

  • Computer Networking

Recommended：

  • Comfortable with interactive shells

Teaching Plan

We organize this course into a 2-week session (8 hours per week). The main contents are listed below:

Topology Task
Switch - basic
VLAN
ARP
Route - static
Route - RIP
Route - OSPF
Switch - advance
NAT

Schedule

Multiple time; multiple locations.

Week Date Lecture Handouts
14 2024/12/02 常用命令与实验工具，双绞线制作，交换机原理，VLAN，ARP，静态路由
15 2024/12/09 RIP，OSPF，三层交换机，NAT，DHCP

Methodology

Problem-solving-oriented, with a primary emphasis on practical skills.

以解决实际问题为导向，主要强调实践技能。

Evaluation

  • Attendance & participation: 10%
  • Practical exercises: 60%
  • Final project: 30%

Textbook

Not mandatory but recommended:

  • J.F. Kurose, K.W. Ross, Computer Networking: a Top Down Approach.

Resource

  • Computer Networking: a Top Down Approach (8th edition)1
  • eNSP simulator installation software2
